libgringotts
------------------------------------------
libGringotts is a small, easy-to-use, thread-safe C library originally
developed for Gringotts; its purpose is to encapsulate data (generic: ASCII,
but also binary data) in an encrypted and compressed structure, to be written
in a file or used elseway. It makes use of strong encryption algorithms, to
ensure the data are as safe as possible, and allow the user to have the
complete control over all the algorithms used in the process.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.6.1-1
  libbz2_1-1.0.6-2
  libgringotts-devel-1.2.1-1bl5
  libgringotts2-1.2.1-1bl5
  libmcrypt4-2.5.8-1
  libmhash2-0.9.9.9-2
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.23.0-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-4
  make-4.2.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://gringotts.berlios.de/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/gringotts.berlios/libgringotts-1.2.1.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libgringotts-1.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libgringotts-1.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libgringotts-1.2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgringotts-1.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgringotts2-1.2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgringotts-devel-1.2.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libgringotts)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libgringotts.README
  /usr/share/doc/libgringotts/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libgringotts/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libgringotts/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libgringotts/README
  /usr/share/doc/libgringotts/TODO
  /usr/share/doc/libgringotts/html/manual.htm

(libgringotts2)
  /usr/bin/cyggringotts-2.dll

(libgringotts-devel)
  /usr/include/libgringotts.h
  /usr/lib/libgringotts.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libgringotts.pc

